nces of time. This aesthetic of cacophony provides an alternative way of expressing social identity and belonging, with an unmarked sense of anonymity providing a counter-form to the dissolving institutions and relationships of neoliberal Japan. Textual Cacophony investigates what it means and feels like to participate in this influential online culture.  aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aIn English.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 06. Mrz 2024) 0aDigital mediaxSocial aspectszJapan. 0aDigital mediaxSocial aspects. 0aInternet videoszJapan. 0aInternet videos. 0aOnline identitieszJapan. 0aOnline identities. 0aOnline social networkszJapan. 0aOnline social networks. 0aSocial media and societyzJapan. 0aSocial media and society. 0aSocial mediazJapan. 0aSocial media. 4aCULTURAL STUDIES. 4aMedia Studies. 7aPOLITICAL SCIENCE / World / Asian.2bisacsh  anico nico, 2channel, linguistics, japanese media, netspeak, social identity, social disconnection, anonymous communication, electronic text, political association.08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertCornell University Press Complete eBook-Package 2023z978311075183308iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertEBOOK PACKAGE COMPLETE 2023 Englishz978311131929208iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertEBOOK PACKAGE COMPLETE 2023z9783111318912oZDB-23-DGG08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertEBOOK PACKAGE Political Science 2023 Englishz978311131925408iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertEBOOK PACKAGE Political Science 2023z9783111318677oZDB-23-PLW40uhttps://doi.org/10.1515/9781501772283?locatt=mode:legacy40uhttps://www.degruyter.com/isbn/9781501772283423Coveruhttps://www.degruyter.com/document/cover/isbn/9781501772283/original  a978-3-11-075183-3  Cornell University Press Complete eBook-Package 2023b2023  a978-3-11-131925-4  EBOOK PACKAGE Polit